9/// \file
10/// This file contains the declarations of the Vectorization Plan base classes:
11/// 1. VPBasicBlock and VPRegionBlock that inherit from a common pure virtual
12/// VPBlockBase, together implementing a Hierarchical CFG;
13/// 2. Pure virtual VPRecipeBase serving as the base class for recipes contained
14/// within VPBasicBlocks;
15/// 3. Pure virtual VPSingleDefRecipe serving as a base class for recipes that
16/// also inherit from VPValue.
17/// 4. VPInstruction, a concrete Recipe and VPUser modeling a single planned
18/// instruction;
19/// 5. The VPlan class holding a candidate for vectorization;
20/// 6. The VPlanPrinter class providing a way to print a plan in dot format;
21/// These are documented in docs/VectorizationPlan.rst.

86/// A helper function that returns the reciprocal of the block probability of
87/// predicated blocks. If we return X, we are assuming the predicated block
88/// will execute once for every X iterations of the loop header.
89///
90/// TODO: We should use actual block probability here, if available. Currently,
91/// we always assume predicated blocks have a 50% chance of executing.
92inline unsigned getReciprocalPredBlockProb() { return 2; }

94/// A range of powers-of-2 vectorization factors with fixed start and
95/// adjustable end. The range includes start and excludes end, e.g.,:
96/// [1, 16) = {1, 2, 4, 8}
97struct VFRange {
98 // A power of 2.
99 const ElementCount Start;
100
101 // A power of 2. If End <= Start range is empty.
102 ElementCount End;
103
104 bool isEmpty() const {
105 return End.getKnownMinValue() <= Start.getKnownMinValue();
106 }
107
108 VFRange(const ElementCount &Start, const ElementCount &End)
109 : Start(Start), End(End) {
110 assert(Start.isScalable() == End.isScalable() &&
111 "Both Start and End should have the same scalable flag");
112 assert(isPowerOf2_32(Start.getKnownMinValue()) &&
113 "Expected Start to be a power of 2");
114 assert(isPowerOf2_32(End.getKnownMinValue()) &&
115 "Expected End to be a power of 2");
116 }
117
118 /// Iterator to iterate over vectorization factors in a VFRange.
119 class iterator
120 : public iterator_facade_base<iterator, std::forward_iterator_tag,
121 ElementCount> {
122 ElementCount VF;
123
124 public:
125 iterator(ElementCount VF) : VF(VF) {}
126
127 bool operator==(const iterator &Other) const { return VF == Other.VF; }
128
129 ElementCount operator*() const { return VF; }
130
131 iterator &operator++() {
132 VF *= 2;
133 return *this;
134 }
135 };
136
137 iterator begin() { return iterator(Start); }
138 iterator end() {
139 assert(isPowerOf2_32(End.getKnownMinValue()));
140 return iterator(End);
141 }
142};

146/// In what follows, the term "input IR" refers to code that is fed into the
147/// vectorizer whereas the term "output IR" refers to code that is generated by
148/// the vectorizer.
149
150/// VPLane provides a way to access lanes in both fixed width and scalable
151/// vectors, where for the latter the lane index sometimes needs calculating
152/// as a runtime expression.
153class VPLane {
154public:
155 /// Kind describes how to interpret Lane.
156 enum class Kind : uint8_t {
157 /// For First, Lane is the index into the first N elements of a
158 /// fixed-vector <N x <ElTy>> or a scalable vector <vscale x N x <ElTy>>.
159 First,
160 /// For ScalableLast, Lane is the offset from the start of the last
161 /// N-element subvector in a scalable vector <vscale x N x <ElTy>>. For
162 /// example, a Lane of 0 corresponds to lane `(vscale - 1) * N`, a Lane of
163 /// 1 corresponds to `((vscale - 1) * N) + 1`, etc.
164 ScalableLast
165 };
166
167private:
168 /// in [0..VF)
169 unsigned Lane;
170
171 /// Indicates how the Lane should be interpreted, as described above.
172 Kind LaneKind;
173
174public:
175 VPLane(unsigned Lane) : Lane(Lane), LaneKind(VPLane::Kind::First) {}
176 VPLane(unsigned Lane, Kind LaneKind) : Lane(Lane), LaneKind(LaneKind) {}
177
178 static VPLane getFirstLane() { return VPLane(0, VPLane::Kind::First); }
179
180 static VPLane getLaneFromEnd(const ElementCount &VF, unsigned Offset) {
181 assert(Offset > 0 && Offset <= VF.getKnownMinValue() &&
182 "trying to extract with invalid offset");
183 unsigned LaneOffset = VF.getKnownMinValue() - Offset;
184 Kind LaneKind;
185 if (VF.isScalable())
186 // In this case 'LaneOffset' refers to the offset from the start of the
187 // last subvector with VF.getKnownMinValue() elements.
188 LaneKind = VPLane::Kind::ScalableLast;
189 else
190 LaneKind = VPLane::Kind::First;
191 return VPLane(LaneOffset, LaneKind);
192 }
193
194 static VPLane getLastLaneForVF(const ElementCount &VF) {
195 return getLaneFromEnd(VF, 1);
196 }
197
198 /// Returns a compile-time known value for the lane index and asserts if the
199 /// lane can only be calculated at runtime.
200 unsigned getKnownLane() const {
201 assert(LaneKind == Kind::First);
202 return Lane;
203 }
204
205 /// Returns an expression describing the lane index that can be used at
206 /// runtime.
207 Value *getAsRuntimeExpr(IRBuilderBase &Builder, const ElementCount &VF) const;
208
209 /// Returns the Kind of lane offset.
210 Kind getKind() const { return LaneKind; }
211
212 /// Returns true if this is the first lane of the whole vector.
213 bool isFirstLane() const { return Lane == 0 && LaneKind == Kind::First; }
214
215 /// Maps the lane to a cache index based on \p VF.
216 unsigned mapToCacheIndex(const ElementCount &VF) const {
217 switch (LaneKind) {
218 case VPLane::Kind::ScalableLast:
219 assert(VF.isScalable() && Lane < VF.getKnownMinValue());
220 return VF.getKnownMinValue() + Lane;
221 default:
222 assert(Lane < VF.getKnownMinValue());
223 return Lane;
224 }
225 }
226
227 /// Returns the maxmimum number of lanes that we are able to consider
228 /// caching for \p VF.
229 static unsigned getNumCachedLanes(const ElementCount &VF) {
230 return VF.getKnownMinValue() * (VF.isScalable() ? 2 : 1);
231 }
232};

234/// VPTransformState holds information passed down when "executing" a VPlan,
235/// needed for generating the output IR.
236struct VPTransformState {
237 VPTransformState(ElementCount VF, unsigned UF, LoopInfo *LI,
238 DominatorTree *DT, IRBuilderBase &Builder,
239 InnerLoopVectorizer *ILV, VPlan *Plan);
240
241 /// The chosen Vectorization Factor of the loop being vectorized.
242 ElementCount VF;
243
244 /// Hold the index to generate specific scalar instructions. Null indicates
245 /// that all instances are to be generated, using either scalar or vector
246 /// instructions.
247 std::optional<VPLane> Lane;
248
249 struct DataState {
250 // Each value from the original loop, when vectorized, is represented by a
251 // vector value in the map.
252 DenseMap<VPValue *, Value *> VPV2Vector;
253
254 DenseMap<VPValue *, SmallVector<Value *, 4>> VPV2Scalars;
255 } Data;
256
257 /// Get the generated vector Value for a given VPValue \p Def if \p IsScalar
258 /// is false, otherwise return the generated scalar. \See set.
259 Value *get(VPValue *Def, bool IsScalar = false);
260
261 /// Get the generated Value for a given VPValue and given Part and Lane.
262 Value *get(VPValue *Def, const VPLane &Lane);
263
264 bool hasVectorValue(VPValue *Def) { return Data.VPV2Vector.contains(Def); }
265
266 bool hasScalarValue(VPValue *Def, VPLane Lane) {
267 auto I = Data.VPV2Scalars.find(Def);
268 if (I == Data.VPV2Scalars.end())
269 return false;
270 unsigned CacheIdx = Lane.mapToCacheIndex(VF);
271 return CacheIdx < I->second.size() && I->second[CacheIdx];
272 }
273
274 /// Set the generated vector Value for a given VPValue, if \p
275 /// IsScalar is false. If \p IsScalar is true, set the scalar in lane 0.
276 void set(VPValue *Def, Value *V, bool IsScalar = false) {
277 if (IsScalar) {
278 set(Def, V, VPLane(0));
279 return;
280 }
281 assert((VF.isScalar() || V->getType()->isVectorTy()) &&
282 "scalar values must be stored as (0, 0)");
283 Data.VPV2Vector[Def] = V;
284 }
285
286 /// Reset an existing vector value for \p Def and a given \p Part.
287 void reset(VPValue *Def, Value *V) {
288 assert(Data.VPV2Vector.contains(Def) && "need to overwrite existing value");
289 Data.VPV2Vector[Def] = V;
290 }
291
292 /// Set the generated scalar \p V for \p Def and the given \p Lane.
293 void set(VPValue *Def, Value *V, const VPLane &Lane) {
294 auto Iter = Data.VPV2Scalars.insert({Def, {}});
295 auto &Scalars = Iter.first->second;
296 unsigned CacheIdx = Lane.mapToCacheIndex(VF);
297 if (Scalars.size() <= CacheIdx)
298 Scalars.resize(CacheIdx + 1);
299 assert(!Scalars[CacheIdx] && "should overwrite existing value");
300 Scalars[CacheIdx] = V;
301 }
302
303 /// Reset an existing scalar value for \p Def and a given \p Lane.
304 void reset(VPValue *Def, Value *V, const VPLane &Lane) {
305 auto Iter = Data.VPV2Scalars.find(Def);
306 assert(Iter != Data.VPV2Scalars.end() &&
307 "need to overwrite existing value");
308 unsigned CacheIdx = Lane.mapToCacheIndex(VF);
309 assert(CacheIdx < Iter->second.size() &&
310 "need to overwrite existing value");
311 Iter->second[CacheIdx] = V;
312 }
313
314 /// Add additional metadata to \p To that was not present on \p Orig.
315 ///
316 /// Currently this is used to add the noalias annotations based on the
317 /// inserted memchecks. Use this for instructions that are *cloned* into the
318 /// vector loop.
319 void addNewMetadata(Instruction *To, const Instruction *Orig);
320
321 /// Add metadata from one instruction to another.
322 ///
323 /// This includes both the original MDs from \p From and additional ones (\see
324 /// addNewMetadata). Use this for *newly created* instructions in the vector
325 /// loop.
326 void addMetadata(Value *To, Instruction *From);
327
328 /// Set the debug location in the builder using the debug location \p DL.
329 void setDebugLocFrom(DebugLoc DL);
330
331 /// Construct the vector value of a scalarized value \p V one lane at a time.
332 void packScalarIntoVectorValue(VPValue *Def, const VPLane &Lane);

334 /// Hold state information used when constructing the CFG of the output IR,
335 /// traversing the VPBasicBlocks and generating corresponding IR BasicBlocks.
336 struct CFGState {
337 /// The previous VPBasicBlock visited. Initially set to null.
338 VPBasicBlock *PrevVPBB = nullptr;
339
340 /// The previous IR BasicBlock created or used. Initially set to the new
341 /// header BasicBlock.
342 BasicBlock *PrevBB = nullptr;
343
344 /// The last IR BasicBlock in the output IR. Set to the exit block of the
345 /// vector loop.
346 BasicBlock *ExitBB = nullptr;
347
348 /// A mapping of each VPBasicBlock to the corresponding BasicBlock. In case
349 /// of replication, maps the BasicBlock of the last replica created.
350 SmallDenseMap<VPBasicBlock *, BasicBlock *> VPBB2IRBB;
351
352 /// Updater for the DominatorTree.
353 DomTreeUpdater DTU;
354
355 CFGState(DominatorTree *DT)
356 : DTU(DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Lazy) {}
357
358 /// Returns the BasicBlock* mapped to the pre-header of the loop region
359 /// containing \p R.
360 BasicBlock *getPreheaderBBFor(VPRecipeBase *R);
361 } CFG;
362
363 /// Hold a pointer to LoopInfo to register new basic blocks in the loop.
364 LoopInfo *LI;
365
366 /// Hold a reference to the IRBuilder used to generate output IR code.
367 IRBuilderBase &Builder;
368
369 /// Hold a pointer to InnerLoopVectorizer to reuse its IR generation methods.
370 InnerLoopVectorizer *ILV;
371
372 /// Pointer to the VPlan code is generated for.
373 VPlan *Plan;
374
375 /// The loop object for the current parent region, or nullptr.
376 Loop *CurrentVectorLoop = nullptr;
377
378 /// LoopVersioning. It's only set up (non-null) if memchecks were
379 /// used.
380 ///
381 /// This is currently only used to add no-alias metadata based on the
382 /// memchecks. The actually versioning is performed manually.
383 LoopVersioning *LVer = nullptr;
384
385 /// Map SCEVs to their expanded values. Populated when executing
386 /// VPExpandSCEVRecipes.
387 DenseMap<const SCEV *, Value *> ExpandedSCEVs;
388
389 /// VPlan-based type analysis.
390 VPTypeAnalysis TypeAnalysis;
391};

393/// VPBlockBase is the building block of the Hierarchical Control-Flow Graph.
394/// A VPBlockBase can be either a VPBasicBlock or a VPRegionBlock.
395class VPBlockBase {
396 friend class VPBlockUtils;
397
398 const unsigned char SubclassID; ///< Subclass identifier (for isa/dyn_cast).
399
400 /// An optional name for the block.
401 std::string Name;
402
403 /// The immediate VPRegionBlock which this VPBlockBase belongs to, or null if
404 /// it is a topmost VPBlockBase.
405 VPRegionBlock *Parent = nullptr;
406
407 /// List of predecessor blocks.
408 SmallVector<VPBlockBase *, 1> Predecessors;
409
410 /// List of successor blocks.
411 SmallVector<VPBlockBase *, 1> Successors;
412
413 /// VPlan containing the block. Can only be set on the entry block of the
414 /// plan.
415 VPlan *Plan = nullptr;
416
417 /// Add \p Successor as the last successor to this block.
418 void appendSuccessor(VPBlockBase *Successor) {
419 assert(Successor && "Cannot add nullptr successor!");
420 Successors.push_back(Successor);
421 }
422
423 /// Add \p Predecessor as the last predecessor to this block.
424 void appendPredecessor(VPBlockBase *Predecessor) {
425 assert(Predecessor && "Cannot add nullptr predecessor!");
426 Predecessors.push_back(Predecessor);
427 }
428
429 /// Remove \p Predecessor from the predecessors of this block.
430 void removePredecessor(VPBlockBase *Predecessor) {
431 auto Pos = find(Predecessors, Predecessor);
432 assert(Pos && "Predecessor does not exist");
433 Predecessors.erase(Pos);
434 }
435
436 /// Remove \p Successor from the successors of this block.
437 void removeSuccessor(VPBlockBase *Successor) {
438 auto Pos = find(Successors, Successor);
439 assert(Pos && "Successor does not exist");
440 Successors.erase(Pos);
441 }
442
443protected:
444 VPBlockBase(const unsigned char SC, const std::string &N)
445 : SubclassID(SC), Name(N) {}
446
447public:
448 /// An enumeration for keeping track of the concrete subclass of VPBlockBase
449 /// that are actually instantiated. Values of this enumeration are kept in the
450 /// SubclassID field of the VPBlockBase objects. They are used for concrete
451 /// type identification.
452 using VPBlockTy = enum { VPRegionBlockSC, VPBasicBlockSC, VPIRBasicBlockSC };
453
454 using VPBlocksTy = SmallVectorImpl<VPBlockBase *>;
455
456 virtual ~VPBlockBase() = default;
457
458 const std::string &getName() const { return Name; }
459
460 void setName(const Twine &newName) { Name = newName.str(); }
461
462 /// \return an ID for the concrete type of this object.
463 /// This is used to implement the classof checks. This should not be used
464 /// for any other purpose, as the values may change as LLVM evolves.
465 unsigned getVPBlockID() const { return SubclassID; }
466
467 VPRegionBlock *getParent() { return Parent; }
468 const VPRegionBlock *getParent() const { return Parent; }
469
470 /// \return A pointer to the plan containing the current block.
471 VPlan *getPlan();
472 const VPlan *getPlan() const;
473
474 /// Sets the pointer of the plan containing the block. The block must be the
475 /// entry block into the VPlan.
476 void setPlan(VPlan *ParentPlan);
477
478 void setParent(VPRegionBlock *P) { Parent = P; }
479
480 /// \return the VPBasicBlock that is the entry of this VPBlockBase,
481 /// recursively, if the latter is a VPRegionBlock. Otherwise, if this
482 /// VPBlockBase is a VPBasicBlock, it is returned.
483 const VPBasicBlock *getEntryBasicBlock() const;
484 VPBasicBlock *getEntryBasicBlock();
485
486 /// \return the VPBasicBlock that is the exiting this VPBlockBase,
487 /// recursively, if the latter is a VPRegionBlock. Otherwise, if this
488 /// VPBlockBase is a VPBasicBlock, it is returned.
489 const VPBasicBlock *getExitingBasicBlock() const;
490 VPBasicBlock *getExitingBasicBlock();
491
492 const VPBlocksTy &getSuccessors() const { return Successors; }
493 VPBlocksTy &getSuccessors() { return Successors; }
494
495 iterator_range<VPBlockBase **> successors() { return Successors; }
496 iterator_range<VPBlockBase **> predecessors() { return Predecessors; }
497
498 const VPBlocksTy &getPredecessors() const { return Predecessors; }
499 VPBlocksTy &getPredecessors() { return Predecessors; }
500
501 /// \return the successor of this VPBlockBase if it has a single successor.
502 /// Otherwise return a null pointer.
503 VPBlockBase *getSingleSuccessor() const {
504 return (Successors.size() == 1 ? *Successors.begin() : nullptr);
505 }
506
507 /// \return the predecessor of this VPBlockBase if it has a single
508 /// predecessor. Otherwise return a null pointer.
509 VPBlockBase *getSinglePredecessor() const {
510 return (Predecessors.size() == 1 ? *Predecessors.begin() : nullptr);
511 }
512
513 size_t getNumSuccessors() const { return Successors.size(); }
514 size_t getNumPredecessors() const { return Predecessors.size(); }
515
516 /// An Enclosing Block of a block B is any block containing B, including B
517 /// itself. \return the closest enclosing block starting from "this", which
518 /// has successors. \return the root enclosing block if all enclosing blocks
519 /// have no successors.
520 VPBlockBase *getEnclosingBlockWithSuccessors();
521
522 /// \return the closest enclosing block starting from "this", which has
523 /// predecessors. \return the root enclosing block if all enclosing blocks
524 /// have no predecessors.
525 VPBlockBase *getEnclosingBlockWithPredecessors();
526
527 /// \return the successors either attached directly to this VPBlockBase or, if
528 /// this VPBlockBase is the exit block of a VPRegionBlock and has no
529 /// successors of its own, search recursively for the first enclosing
530 /// VPRegionBlock that has successors and return them. If no such
531 /// VPRegionBlock exists, return the (empty) successors of the topmost
532 /// VPBlockBase reached.
533 const VPBlocksTy &getHierarchicalSuccessors() {
534 return getEnclosingBlockWithSuccessors()->getSuccessors();
535 }
536
537 /// \return the hierarchical successor of this VPBlockBase if it has a single
538 /// hierarchical successor. Otherwise return a null pointer.
539 VPBlockBase *getSingleHierarchicalSuccessor() {
540 return getEnclosingBlockWithSuccessors()->getSingleSuccessor();
541 }
542
543 /// \return the predecessors either attached directly to this VPBlockBase or,
544 /// if this VPBlockBase is the entry block of a VPRegionBlock and has no
545 /// predecessors of its own, search recursively for the first enclosing
546 /// VPRegionBlock that has predecessors and return them. If no such
547 /// VPRegionBlock exists, return the (empty) predecessors of the topmost
548 /// VPBlockBase reached.
549 const VPBlocksTy &getHierarchicalPredecessors() {
550 return getEnclosingBlockWithPredecessors()->getPredecessors();
551 }
552
553 /// \return the hierarchical predecessor of this VPBlockBase if it has a
554 /// single hierarchical predecessor. Otherwise return a null pointer.
555 VPBlockBase *getSingleHierarchicalPredecessor() {
556 return getEnclosingBlockWithPredecessors()->getSinglePredecessor();
557 }
558
559 /// Set a given VPBlockBase \p Successor as the single successor of this
560 /// VPBlockBase. This VPBlockBase is not added as predecessor of \p Successor.
561 /// This VPBlockBase must have no successors.
562 void setOneSuccessor(VPBlockBase *Successor) {
563 assert(Successors.empty() && "Setting one successor when others exist.");
564 assert(Successor->getParent() == getParent() &&
565 "connected blocks must have the same parent");
566 appendSuccessor(Successor);
567 }
568
569 /// Set two given VPBlockBases \p IfTrue and \p IfFalse to be the two
570 /// successors of this VPBlockBase. This VPBlockBase is not added as
571 /// predecessor of \p IfTrue or \p IfFalse. This VPBlockBase must have no
572 /// successors.
573 void setTwoSuccessors(VPBlockBase *IfTrue, VPBlockBase *IfFalse) {
574 assert(Successors.empty() && "Setting two successors when others exist.");
575 appendSuccessor(IfTrue);
576 appendSuccessor(IfFalse);
577 }
578
579 /// Set each VPBasicBlock in \p NewPreds as predecessor of this VPBlockBase.
580 /// This VPBlockBase must have no predecessors. This VPBlockBase is not added
581 /// as successor of any VPBasicBlock in \p NewPreds.
582 void setPredecessors(ArrayRef<VPBlockBase *> NewPreds) {
583 assert(Predecessors.empty() && "Block predecessors already set.");
584 for (auto *Pred : NewPreds)
585 appendPredecessor(Pred);
586 }
587
588 /// Set each VPBasicBlock in \p NewSuccss as successor of this VPBlockBase.
589 /// This VPBlockBase must have no successors. This VPBlockBase is not added
590 /// as predecessor of any VPBasicBlock in \p NewSuccs.
591 void setSuccessors(ArrayRef<VPBlockBase *> NewSuccs) {
592 assert(Successors.empty() && "Block successors already set.");
593 for (auto *Succ : NewSuccs)
594 appendSuccessor(Succ);
595 }
596
597 /// Remove all the predecessor of this block.
598 void clearPredecessors() { Predecessors.clear(); }
599
600 /// Remove all the successors of this block.
601 void clearSuccessors() { Successors.clear(); }
602
603 /// The method which generates the output IR that correspond to this
604 /// VPBlockBase, thereby "executing" the VPlan.
605 virtual void execute(VPTransformState *State) = 0;
606
607 /// Return the cost of the block.
608 virtual InstructionCost cost(ElementCount VF, VPCostContext &Ctx) = 0;
609
610 /// Delete all blocks reachable from a given VPBlockBase, inclusive.
611 static void deleteCFG(VPBlockBase *Entry);
612
613 /// Return true if it is legal to hoist instructions into this block.
614 bool isLegalToHoistInto() {
615 // There are currently no constraints that prevent an instruction to be
616 // hoisted into a VPBlockBase.
617 return true;
618 }
619
620 /// Replace all operands of VPUsers in the block with \p NewValue and also
621 /// replaces all uses of VPValues defined in the block with NewValue.
622 virtual void dropAllReferences(VPValue *NewValue) = 0;
623
624#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
625 void printAsOperand(raw_ostream &OS, bool PrintType) const {
626 OS << getName();
627 }
628
629 /// Print plain-text dump of this VPBlockBase to \p O, prefixing all lines
630 /// with \p Indent. \p SlotTracker is used to print unnamed VPValue's using
631 /// consequtive numbers.
632 ///
633 /// Note that the numbering is applied to the whole VPlan, so printing
634 /// individual blocks is consistent with the whole VPlan printing.
635 virtual void print(raw_ostream &O, const Twine &Indent,
636 VPSlotTracker &SlotTracker) const = 0;
637
638 /// Print plain-text dump of this VPlan to \p O.
639 void print(raw_ostream &O) const {
640 VPSlotTracker SlotTracker(getPlan());
641 print(O, "", SlotTracker);
642 }
643
644 /// Print the successors of this block to \p O, prefixing all lines with \p
645 /// Indent.
646 void printSuccessors(raw_ostream &O, const Twine &Indent) const;
647
648 /// Dump this VPBlockBase to dbgs().
649 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void dump() const { print(dbgs()); }
650#endif
651
652 /// Clone the current block and it's recipes without updating the operands of
653 /// the cloned recipes, including all blocks in the single-entry single-exit
654 /// region for VPRegionBlocks.
655 virtual VPBlockBase *clone() = 0;
656};
657
658/// A value that is used outside the VPlan. The operand of the user needs to be
659/// added to the associated phi node. The incoming block from VPlan is
660/// determined by where the VPValue is defined: if it is defined by a recipe
661/// outside a region, its parent block is used, otherwise the middle block is
662/// used.
663class VPLiveOut : public VPUser {
664 PHINode *Phi;
665
666public:
667 VPLiveOut(PHINode *Phi, VPValue *Op)
668 : VPUser({Op}, VPUser::VPUserID::LiveOut), Phi(Phi) {}
669
670 static inline bool classof(const VPUser *U) {
671 return U->getVPUserID() == VPUser::VPUserID::LiveOut;
672 }
673
674 /// Fix the wrapped phi node. This means adding an incoming value to exit
675 /// block phi's from the vector loop via middle block (values from scalar loop
676 /// already reach these phi's), and updating the value to scalar header phi's
677 /// from the scalar preheader.
678 void fixPhi(VPlan &Plan, VPTransformState &State);
679
680 /// Returns true if the VPLiveOut uses scalars of operand \p Op.
681 bool usesScalars(const VPValue *Op) const override {
682 assert(is_contained(operands(), Op) &&
683 "Op must be an operand of the recipe");
684 return true;
685 }
686
687 PHINode *getPhi() const { return Phi; }
688
689 /// Live-outs are marked as only using the first part during the transition
690 /// to unrolling directly on VPlan.
691 /// TODO: Remove after unroller transition.
692 bool onlyFirstPartUsed(const VPValue *Op) const override { return true; }
693
694#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
695 /// Print the VPLiveOut to \p O.
696 void print(raw_ostream &O, VPSlotTracker &SlotTracker) const;
697#endif
698};

700/// Struct to hold various analysis needed for cost computations.
701struct VPCostContext {
702 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI;
703 const TargetLibraryInfo &TLI;
704 VPTypeAnalysis Types;
705 LLVMContext &LLVMCtx;
706 LoopVectorizationCostModel &CM;
707 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 8> SkipCostComputation;
708
709 VPCostContext(const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, const TargetLibraryInfo &TLI,
710 Type *CanIVTy, LoopVectorizationCostModel &CM)
711 : TTI(TTI), TLI(TLI), Types(CanIVTy), LLVMCtx(CanIVTy->getContext()),
712 CM(CM) {}
713
714 /// Return the cost for \p UI with \p VF using the legacy cost model as
715 /// fallback until computing the cost of all recipes migrates to VPlan.
716 InstructionCost getLegacyCost(Instruction *UI, ElementCount VF) const;
717
718 /// Return true if the cost for \p UI shouldn't be computed, e.g. because it
719 /// has already been pre-computed.
720 bool skipCostComputation(Instruction *UI, bool IsVector) const;
721};

723/// VPRecipeBase is a base class modeling a sequence of one or more output IR
724/// instructions. VPRecipeBase owns the VPValues it defines through VPDef
725/// and is responsible for deleting its defined values. Single-value
726/// recipes must inherit from VPSingleDef instead of inheriting from both
727/// VPRecipeBase and VPValue separately.
728class VPRecipeBase : public ilist_node_with_parent<VPRecipeBase, VPBasicBlock>,
729 public VPDef,
730 public VPUser {
731 friend VPBasicBlock;
732 friend class VPBlockUtils;
733
734 /// Each VPRecipe belongs to a single VPBasicBlock.
735 VPBasicBlock *Parent = nullptr;
736
737 /// The debug location for the recipe.
738 DebugLoc DL;
739
740public:
741 VPRecipeBase(const unsigned char SC, ArrayRef<VPValue *> Operands,
742 DebugLoc DL = {})
743 : VPDef(SC), VPUser(Operands, VPUser::VPUserID::Recipe), DL(DL) {}
744
745 template <typename IterT>
746 VPRecipeBase(const unsigned char SC, iterator_range<IterT> Operands,
747 DebugLoc DL = {})
748 : VPDef(SC), VPUser(Operands, VPUser::VPUserID::Recipe), DL(DL) {}
749 virtual ~VPRecipeBase() = default;
750
751 /// Clone the current recipe.
752 virtual VPRecipeBase *clone() = 0;
753
754 /// \return the VPBasicBlock which this VPRecipe belongs to.
755 VPBasicBlock *getParent() { return Parent; }
756 const VPBasicBlock *getParent() const { return Parent; }
757
758 /// The method which generates the output IR instructions that correspond to
759 /// this VPRecipe, thereby "executing" the VPlan.
760 virtual void execute(VPTransformState &State) = 0;
761
762 /// Return the cost of this recipe, taking into account if the cost
763 /// computation should be skipped and the ForceTargetInstructionCost flag.
764 /// Also takes care of printing the cost for debugging.
765 InstructionCost cost(ElementCount VF, VPCostContext &Ctx);
766
767 /// Insert an unlinked recipe into a basic block immediately before
768 /// the specified recipe.
769 void insertBefore(VPRecipeBase *InsertPos);
770 /// Insert an unlinked recipe into \p BB immediately before the insertion
771 /// point \p IP;
772 void insertBefore(VPBasicBlock &BB, iplist<VPRecipeBase>::iterator IP);
773
774 /// Insert an unlinked Recipe into a basic block immediately after
775 /// the specified Recipe.
776 void insertAfter(VPRecipeBase *InsertPos);
777
778 /// Unlink this recipe from its current VPBasicBlock and insert it into
779 /// the VPBasicBlock that MovePos lives in, right after MovePos.
780 void moveAfter(VPRecipeBase *MovePos);
781
782 /// Unlink this recipe and insert into BB before I.
783 ///
784 /// \pre I is a valid iterator into BB.
785 void moveBefore(VPBasicBlock &BB, iplist<VPRecipeBase>::iterator I);
786
787 /// This method unlinks 'this' from the containing basic block, but does not
788 /// delete it.
789 void removeFromParent();
790
791 /// This method unlinks 'this' from the containing basic block and deletes it.
792 ///
793 /// \returns an iterator pointing to the element after the erased one
794 iplist<VPRecipeBase>::iterator eraseFromParent();
795
796 /// Method to support type inquiry through isa, cast, and dyn_cast.
797 static inline bool classof(const VPDef *D) {
798 // All VPDefs are also VPRecipeBases.
799 return true;
800 }
801
802 static inline bool classof(const VPUser *U) {
803 return U->getVPUserID() == VPUser::VPUserID::Recipe;
804 }
805
806 /// Returns true if the recipe may have side-effects.
807 bool mayHaveSideEffects() const;
808
809 /// Returns true for PHI-like recipes.
810 bool isPhi() const {
811 return getVPDefID() >= VPFirstPHISC && getVPDefID() <= VPLastPHISC;
812 }
813
814 /// Returns true if the recipe may read from memory.
815 bool mayReadFromMemory() const;
816
817 /// Returns true if the recipe may write to memory.
818 bool mayWriteToMemory() const;
819
820 /// Returns true if the recipe may read from or write to memory.
821 bool mayReadOrWriteMemory() const {
822 return mayReadFromMemory() || mayWriteToMemory();
823 }
824
825 /// Returns the debug location of the recipe.
826 DebugLoc getDebugLoc() const { return DL; }
827
828protected:
829 /// Compute the cost of this recipe either using a recipe's specialized
830 /// implementation or using the legacy cost model and the underlying
831 /// instructions.
832 virtual InstructionCost computeCost(ElementCount VF,
833 VPCostContext &Ctx) const;
834};

856/// VPSingleDef is a base class for recipes for modeling a sequence of one or
857/// more output IR that define a single result VPValue.

871 DebugLoc DL = {})
872 : VPRecipeBase(SC, Operands, DL), VPValue(this, UV) {}

874 static inline bool classof(const VPRecipeBase *R) {

876 case VPRecipeBase::VPDerivedIVSC:
877 case VPRecipeBase::VPEVLBasedIVPHISC:
878 case VPRecipeBase::VPExpandSCEVSC:
879 case VPRecipeBase::VPInstructionSC:
880 case VPRecipeBase::VPReductionEVLSC:
881 case VPRecipeBase::VPReductionSC:
882 case VPRecipeBase::VPReplicateSC:
883 case VPRecipeBase::VPScalarIVStepsSC:
884 case VPRecipeBase::VPVectorPointerSC:
885 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenCallSC:
886 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenCanonicalIVSC:
887 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenCastSC:
888 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenGEPSC:
889 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenSC:
890 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenEVLSC:
891 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenSelectSC:
892 case VPRecipeBase::VPBlendSC:
893 case VPRecipeBase::VPPredInstPHISC:
894 case VPRecipeBase::VPCanonicalIVPHISC:
895 case VPRecipeBase::VPActiveLaneMaskPHISC:
896 case VPRecipeBase::VPFirstOrderRecurrencePHISC:
897 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenPHISC:
898 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenIntOrFpInductionSC:
899 case VPRecipeBase::VPWidenPointerInductionSC:
900 case VPRecipeBase::VPReductionPHISC:
901 case VPRecipeBase::VPScalarCastSC:

903 case VPRecipeBase::VPBranchOnMaskSC:
904 case VPRecipeBase::VPInterleaveSC:
905 case VPRecipeBase::VPIRInstructionSC:

934/// Class to record LLVM IR flag for a recipe along with it.
935class VPRecipeWithIRFlags : public VPSingleDefRecipe {
936 enum class OperationType : unsigned char {
937 Cmp,
938 OverflowingBinOp,
939 DisjointOp,
940 PossiblyExactOp,
941 GEPOp,
942 FPMathOp,
943 NonNegOp,
944 Other
945 };
946
947public:
948 struct WrapFlagsTy {
949 char HasNUW : 1;
950 char HasNSW : 1;
951
952 WrapFlagsTy(bool HasNUW, bool HasNSW) : HasNUW(HasNUW), HasNSW(HasNSW) {}
953 };
954
955 struct DisjointFlagsTy {
956 char IsDisjoint : 1;
957 DisjointFlagsTy(bool IsDisjoint) : IsDisjoint(IsDisjoint) {}
958 };
959
960protected:
961 struct GEPFlagsTy {
962 char IsInBounds : 1;
963 GEPFlagsTy(bool IsInBounds) : IsInBounds(IsInBounds) {}
964 };
965
966private:
967 struct ExactFlagsTy {
968 char IsExact : 1;
969 };
970 struct NonNegFlagsTy {
971 char NonNeg : 1;
972 };
973 struct FastMathFlagsTy {
974 char AllowReassoc : 1;
975 char NoNaNs : 1;
976 char NoInfs : 1;
977 char NoSignedZeros : 1;
978 char AllowReciprocal : 1;
979 char AllowContract : 1;
980 char ApproxFunc : 1;
981
982 FastMathFlagsTy(const FastMathFlags &FMF);
983 };
984
985 OperationType OpType;
986
987 union {
988 CmpInst::Predicate CmpPredicate;
989 WrapFlagsTy WrapFlags;
990 DisjointFlagsTy DisjointFlags;
991 ExactFlagsTy ExactFlags;
992 GEPFlagsTy GEPFlags;
993 NonNegFlagsTy NonNegFlags;
994 FastMathFlagsTy FMFs;
995 unsigned AllFlags;
996 };
997
998protected:
999 void transferFlags(VPRecipeWithIRFlags &Other) {
1000 OpType = Other.OpType;
1001 AllFlags = Other.AllFlags;
1002 }
1003
1004public:
1005 template <typename IterT>
1006 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands, DebugLoc DL = {})
1007 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, DL) {
1008 OpType = OperationType::Other;
1009 AllFlags = 0;
1010 }
1011
1012 template <typename IterT>
1013 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands, Instruction &I)
1014 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, &I, I.getDebugLoc()) {
1015 if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(&I)) {
1016 OpType = OperationType::Cmp;
1017 CmpPredicate = Op->getPredicate();
1018 } else if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<PossiblyDisjointInst>(&I)) {
1019 OpType = OperationType::DisjointOp;
1020 DisjointFlags.IsDisjoint = Op->isDisjoint();
1021 } else if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(&I)) {
1022 OpType = OperationType::OverflowingBinOp;
1023 WrapFlags = {Op->hasNoUnsignedWrap(), Op->hasNoSignedWrap()};
1024 } else if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<PossiblyExactOperator>(&I)) {
1025 OpType = OperationType::PossiblyExactOp;
1026 ExactFlags.IsExact = Op->isExact();
1027 } else if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(&I)) {
1028 OpType = OperationType::GEPOp;
1029 GEPFlags.IsInBounds = GEP->isInBounds();
1030 } else if (auto *PNNI = dyn_cast<PossiblyNonNegInst>(&I)) {
1031 OpType = OperationType::NonNegOp;
1032 NonNegFlags.NonNeg = PNNI->hasNonNeg();
1033 } else if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(&I)) {
1034 OpType = OperationType::FPMathOp;
1035 FMFs = Op->getFastMathFlags();
1036 } else {
1037 OpType = OperationType::Other;
1038 AllFlags = 0;
1039 }
1040 }
1041
1042 template <typename IterT>
1043 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands,
1044 CmpInst::Predicate Pred, DebugLoc DL = {})
1045 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, DL), OpType(OperationType::Cmp),
1046 CmpPredicate(Pred) {}
1047
1048 template <typename IterT>
1049 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands,
1050 WrapFlagsTy WrapFlags, DebugLoc DL = {})
1051 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, DL),
1052 OpType(OperationType::OverflowingBinOp), WrapFlags(WrapFlags) {}
1053
1054 template <typename IterT>
1055 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands,
1056 FastMathFlags FMFs, DebugLoc DL = {})
1057 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, DL), OpType(OperationType::FPMathOp),
1058 FMFs(FMFs) {}
1059
1060 template <typename IterT>
1061 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands,
1062 DisjointFlagsTy DisjointFlags, DebugLoc DL = {})
1063 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, DL), OpType(OperationType::DisjointOp),
1064 DisjointFlags(DisjointFlags) {}
1065
1066protected:
1067 template <typename IterT>
1068 VPRecipeWithIRFlags(const unsigned char SC, IterT Operands,
1069 GEPFlagsTy GEPFlags, DebugLoc DL = {})
1070 : VPSingleDefRecipe(SC, Operands, DL), OpType(OperationType::GEPOp),
1071 GEPFlags(GEPFlags) {}
1072
1073public:
1074 static inline bool classof(const VPRecipeBase *R) {
1075 return R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPInstructionSC ||
1076 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenSC ||
1077 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenEVLSC ||
1078 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenGEPSC ||
1079 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenCastSC ||
1080 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPReplicateSC ||
1081 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPVectorPointerSC;
1082 }
1083
1084 static inline bool classof(const VPUser *U) {
1085 auto *R = dyn_cast<VPRecipeBase>(U);
1086 return R && classof(R);
1087 }
1088
1089 /// Drop all poison-generating flags.
1090 void dropPoisonGeneratingFlags() {
1091 // NOTE: This needs to be kept in-sync with
1092 // Instruction::dropPoisonGeneratingFlags.
1093 switch (OpType) {
1094 case OperationType::OverflowingBinOp:
1095 WrapFlags.HasNUW = false;
1096 WrapFlags.HasNSW = false;
1097 break;
1098 case OperationType::DisjointOp:
1099 DisjointFlags.IsDisjoint = false;
1100 break;
1101 case OperationType::PossiblyExactOp:
1102 ExactFlags.IsExact = false;
1103 break;
1104 case OperationType::GEPOp:
1105 GEPFlags.IsInBounds = false;
1106 break;
1107 case OperationType::FPMathOp:
1108 FMFs.NoNaNs = false;
1109 FMFs.NoInfs = false;
1110 break;
1111 case OperationType::NonNegOp:
1112 NonNegFlags.NonNeg = false;
1113 break;
1114 case OperationType::Cmp:
1115 case OperationType::Other:
1116 break;
1117 }
1118 }
1119
1120 /// Set the IR flags for \p I.
1121 void setFlags(Instruction *I) const {
1122 switch (OpType) {
1123 case OperationType::OverflowingBinOp:
1124 I->setHasNoUnsignedWrap(WrapFlags.HasNUW);
1125 I->setHasNoSignedWrap(WrapFlags.HasNSW);
1126 break;
1127 case OperationType::DisjointOp:
1128 cast<PossiblyDisjointInst>(I)->setIsDisjoint(DisjointFlags.IsDisjoint);
1129 break;
1130 case OperationType::PossiblyExactOp:
1131 I->setIsExact(ExactFlags.IsExact);
1132 break;
1133 case OperationType::GEPOp:
1134 // TODO(gep_nowrap): Track the full GEPNoWrapFlags in VPlan.
1135 cast<GetElementPtrInst>(I)->setNoWrapFlags(
1136 GEPFlags.IsInBounds ? GEPNoWrapFlags::inBounds()
1137 : GEPNoWrapFlags::none());
1138 break;
1139 case OperationType::FPMathOp:
1140 I->setHasAllowReassoc(FMFs.AllowReassoc);
1141 I->setHasNoNaNs(FMFs.NoNaNs);
1142 I->setHasNoInfs(FMFs.NoInfs);
1143 I->setHasNoSignedZeros(FMFs.NoSignedZeros);
1144 I->setHasAllowReciprocal(FMFs.AllowReciprocal);
1145 I->setHasAllowContract(FMFs.AllowContract);
1146 I->setHasApproxFunc(FMFs.ApproxFunc);
1147 break;
1148 case OperationType::NonNegOp:
1149 I->setNonNeg(NonNegFlags.NonNeg);
1150 break;
1151 case OperationType::Cmp:
1152 case OperationType::Other:
1153 break;
1154 }
1155 }
1156
1157 CmpInst::Predicate getPredicate() const {
1158 assert(OpType == OperationType::Cmp &&
1159 "recipe doesn't have a compare predicate");
1160 return CmpPredicate;
1161 }
1162
1163 bool isInBounds() const {
1164 assert(OpType == OperationType::GEPOp &&
1165 "recipe doesn't have inbounds flag");
1166 return GEPFlags.IsInBounds;
1167 }
1168
1169 /// Returns true if the recipe has fast-math flags.
1170 bool hasFastMathFlags() const { return OpType == OperationType::FPMathOp; }
1171
1172 FastMathFlags getFastMathFlags() const;
1173
1174 bool hasNoUnsignedWrap() const {
1175 assert(OpType == OperationType::OverflowingBinOp &&
1176 "recipe doesn't have a NUW flag");
1177 return WrapFlags.HasNUW;
1178 }
1179
1180 bool hasNoSignedWrap() const {
1181 assert(OpType == OperationType::OverflowingBinOp &&
1182 "recipe doesn't have a NSW flag");
1183 return WrapFlags.HasNSW;
1184 }
1185
1186 bool isDisjoint() const {
1187 assert(OpType == OperationType::DisjointOp &&
1188 "recipe cannot have a disjoing flag");
1189 return DisjointFlags.IsDisjoint;
1190 }
1191
1192#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
1193 void printFlags(raw_ostream &O) const;
1194#endif
1195};

1209/// This is a concrete Recipe that models a single VPlan-level instruction.
1210/// While as any Recipe it may generate a sequence of IR instructions when
1211/// executed, these instructions would always form a single-def expression as
1212/// the VPInstruction is also a single def-use vertex.
1213class VPInstruction : public VPRecipeWithIRFlags,
1214 public VPUnrollPartAccessor<1> {
1215 friend class VPlanSlp;
1216
1217public:
1218 /// VPlan opcodes, extending LLVM IR with idiomatics instructions.
1219 enum {
1220 FirstOrderRecurrenceSplice =
1221 Instruction::OtherOpsEnd + 1, // Combines the incoming and previous
1222 // values of a first-order recurrence.
1223 Not,
1224 SLPLoad,
1225 SLPStore,
1226 ActiveLaneMask,
1227 ExplicitVectorLength,
1228 /// Creates a scalar phi in a leaf VPBB with a single predecessor in VPlan.
1229 /// The first operand is the incoming value from the predecessor in VPlan,
1230 /// the second operand is the incoming value for all other predecessors
1231 /// (which are currently not modeled in VPlan).
1232 ResumePhi,
1233 CalculateTripCountMinusVF,
1234 // Increment the canonical IV separately for each unrolled part.
1235 CanonicalIVIncrementForPart,
1236 BranchOnCount,
1237 BranchOnCond,
1238 ComputeReductionResult,
1239 // Takes the VPValue to extract from as first operand and the lane or part
1240 // to extract as second operand, counting from the end starting with 1 for
1241 // last. The second operand must be a positive constant and <= VF.
1242 ExtractFromEnd,
1243 LogicalAnd, // Non-poison propagating logical And.
1244 // Add an offset in bytes (second operand) to a base pointer (first
1245 // operand). Only generates scalar values (either for the first lane only or
1246 // for all lanes, depending on its uses).
1247 PtrAdd,
1248 };
1249
1250private:
1251 typedef unsigned char OpcodeTy;
1252 OpcodeTy Opcode;
1253
1254 /// An optional name that can be used for the generated IR instruction.
1255 const std::string Name;
1256
1257 /// Returns true if this VPInstruction generates scalar values for all lanes.
1258 /// Most VPInstructions generate a single value per part, either vector or
1259 /// scalar. VPReplicateRecipe takes care of generating multiple (scalar)
1260 /// values per all lanes, stemming from an original ingredient. This method
1261 /// identifies the (rare) cases of VPInstructions that do so as well, w/o an
1262 /// underlying ingredient.
1263 bool doesGeneratePerAllLanes() const;
1264
1265 /// Returns true if we can generate a scalar for the first lane only if
1266 /// needed.
1267 bool canGenerateScalarForFirstLane() const;
1268
1269 /// Utility methods serving execute(): generates a single vector instance of
1270 /// the modeled instruction. \returns the generated value. . In some cases an
1271 /// existing value is returned rather than a generated one.
1272 Value *generate(VPTransformState &State);
1273
1274 /// Utility methods serving execute(): generates a scalar single instance of
1275 /// the modeled instruction for a given lane. \returns the scalar generated
1276 /// value for lane \p Lane.
1277 Value *generatePerLane(VPTransformState &State, const VPLane &Lane);
1278
1279#if !defined(NDEBUG)
1280 /// Return true if the VPInstruction is a floating point math operation, i.e.
1281 /// has fast-math flags.
1282 bool isFPMathOp() const;
1283#endif
1284
1285public:
1286 VPInstruction(unsigned Opcode, ArrayRef<VPValue *> Operands, DebugLoc DL,
1287 const Twine &Name = "")
1288 : VPRecipeWithIRFlags(VPDef::VPInstructionSC, Operands, DL),
1289 Opcode(Opcode), Name(Name.str()) {}
1290
1291 VPInstruction(unsigned Opcode, std::initializer_list<VPValue *> Operands,
1292 DebugLoc DL = {}, const Twine &Name = "")
1293 : VPInstruction(Opcode, ArrayRef<VPValue *>(Operands), DL, Name) {}
1294
1295 VPInstruction(unsigned Opcode, CmpInst::Predicate Pred, VPValue *A,
1296 VPValue *B, DebugLoc DL = {}, const Twine &Name = "");
1297
1298 VPInstruction(unsigned Opcode, std::initializer_list<VPValue *> Operands,
1299 WrapFlagsTy WrapFlags, DebugLoc DL = {}, const Twine &Name = "")
1300 : VPRecipeWithIRFlags(VPDef::VPInstructionSC, Operands, WrapFlags, DL),
1301 Opcode(Opcode), Name(Name.str()) {}
1302
1303 VPInstruction(unsigned Opcode, std::initializer_list<VPValue *> Operands,
1304 DisjointFlagsTy DisjointFlag, DebugLoc DL = {},
1305 const Twine &Name = "")
1306 : VPRecipeWithIRFlags(VPDef::VPInstructionSC, Operands, DisjointFlag, DL),
1307 Opcode(Opcode), Name(Name.str()) {
1308 assert(Opcode == Instruction::Or && "only OR opcodes can be disjoint");
1309 }
1310
1311 VPInstruction(unsigned Opcode, std::initializer_list<VPValue *> Operands,
1312 FastMathFlags FMFs, DebugLoc DL = {}, const Twine &Name = "");
1313
1314 VP_CLASSOF_IMPL(VPDef::VPInstructionSC)
1315
1316 VPInstruction *clone() override {
1317 SmallVector<VPValue *, 2> Operands(operands());
1318 auto *New = new VPInstruction(Opcode, Operands, getDebugLoc(), Name);
1319 New->transferFlags(*this);
1320 return New;
1321 }

1323 unsigned getOpcode() const { return Opcode; }
1324
1325 /// Generate the instruction.
1326 /// TODO: We currently execute only per-part unless a specific instance is
1327 /// provided.
1328 void execute(VPTransformState &State) override;
1329
1330#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
1331 /// Print the VPInstruction to \p O.
1332 void print(raw_ostream &O, const Twine &Indent,
1333 VPSlotTracker &SlotTracker) const override;
1334
1335 /// Print the VPInstruction to dbgs() (for debugging).
1336 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void dump() const;
1337#endif
1338
1339 /// Return true if this instruction may modify memory.
1340 bool mayWriteToMemory() const {
1341 // TODO: we can use attributes of the called function to rule out memory
1342 // modifications.
1343 return Opcode == Instruction::Store || Opcode == Instruction::Call ||
1344 Opcode == Instruction::Invoke || Opcode == SLPStore;
1345 }
1346
1347 bool hasResult() const {
1348 // CallInst may or may not have a result, depending on the called function.
1349 // Conservatively return calls have results for now.
1350 switch (getOpcode()) {
1351 case Instruction::Ret:
1352 case Instruction::Br:
1353 case Instruction::Store:
1354 case Instruction::Switch:
1355 case Instruction::IndirectBr:
1356 case Instruction::Resume:
1357 case Instruction::CatchRet:
1358 case Instruction::Unreachable:
1359 case Instruction::Fence:
1360 case Instruction::AtomicRMW:
1361 case VPInstruction::BranchOnCond:
1362 case VPInstruction::BranchOnCount:
1363 return false;
1364 default:
1365 return true;
1366 }
1367 }

1369 /// Returns true if the recipe only uses the first lane of operand \p Op.
1370 bool onlyFirstLaneUsed(const VPValue *Op) const override;
1371
1372 /// Returns true if the recipe only uses the first part of operand \p Op.
1373 bool onlyFirstPartUsed(const VPValue *Op) const override;
1374
1375 /// Returns true if this VPInstruction produces a scalar value from a vector,
1376 /// e.g. by performing a reduction or extracting a lane.
1377 bool isVectorToScalar() const;
1378
1379 /// Returns true if this VPInstruction's operands are single scalars and the
1380 /// result is also a single scalar.
1381 bool isSingleScalar() const;

1832/// A pure virtual base class for all recipes modeling header phis, including
1833/// phis for first order recurrences, pointer inductions and reductions. The
1834/// start value is the first operand of the recipe and the incoming value from
1835/// the backedge is the second operand.
1836///
1837/// Inductions are modeled using the following sub-classes:
1838/// * VPCanonicalIVPHIRecipe: Canonical scalar induction of the vector loop,
1839/// starting at a specified value (zero for the main vector loop, the resume
1840/// value for the epilogue vector loop) and stepping by 1. The induction
1841/// controls exiting of the vector loop by comparing against the vector trip
1842/// count. Produces a single scalar PHI for the induction value per
1843/// iteration.
1844/// * VPWidenIntOrFpInductionRecipe: Generates vector values for integer and
1845/// floating point inductions with arbitrary start and step values. Produces
1846/// a vector PHI per-part.
1847/// * VPDerivedIVRecipe: Converts the canonical IV value to the corresponding
1848/// value of an IV with different start and step values. Produces a single
1849/// scalar value per iteration
1850/// * VPScalarIVStepsRecipe: Generates scalar values per-lane based on a
1851/// canonical or derived induction.
1852/// * VPWidenPointerInductionRecipe: Generate vector and scalar values for a
1853/// pointer induction. Produces either a vector PHI per-part or scalar values
1854/// per-lane based on the canonical induction.
1855class VPHeaderPHIRecipe : public VPSingleDefRecipe {
1856protected:
1857 VPHeaderPHIRecipe(unsigned char VPDefID, Instruction *UnderlyingInstr,
1858 VPValue *Start = nullptr, DebugLoc DL = {})
1859 : VPSingleDefRecipe(VPDefID, ArrayRef<VPValue *>(), UnderlyingInstr, DL) {
1860 if (Start)
1861 addOperand(Start);
1862 }
1863
1864public:
1865 ~VPHeaderPHIRecipe() override = default;
1866
1867 /// Method to support type inquiry through isa, cast, and dyn_cast.
1868 static inline bool classof(const VPRecipeBase *B) {
1869 return B->getVPDefID() >= VPDef::VPFirstHeaderPHISC &&
1870 B->getVPDefID() <= VPDef::VPLastHeaderPHISC;
1871 }
1872 static inline bool classof(const VPValue *V) {
1873 auto *B = V->getDefiningRecipe();
1874 return B && B->getVPDefID() >= VPRecipeBase::VPFirstHeaderPHISC &&
1875 B->getVPDefID() <= VPRecipeBase::VPLastHeaderPHISC;
1876 }
1877
1878 /// Generate the phi nodes.
1879 void execute(VPTransformState &State) override = 0;
1880
1881#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
1882 /// Print the recipe.
1883 void print(raw_ostream &O, const Twine &Indent,
1884 VPSlotTracker &SlotTracker) const override = 0;
1885#endif
1886
1887 /// Returns the start value of the phi, if one is set.
1888 VPValue *getStartValue() {
1889 return getNumOperands() == 0 ? nullptr : getOperand(0);
1890 }
1891 VPValue *getStartValue() const {
1892 return getNumOperands() == 0 ? nullptr : getOperand(0);
1893 }
1894
1895 /// Update the start value of the recipe.
1896 void setStartValue(VPValue *V) { setOperand(0, V); }
1897
1898 /// Returns the incoming value from the loop backedge.
1899 virtual VPValue *getBackedgeValue() {
1900 return getOperand(1);
1901 }
1902
1903 /// Returns the backedge value as a recipe. The backedge value is guaranteed
1904 /// to be a recipe.
1905 virtual VPRecipeBase &getBackedgeRecipe() {
1906 return *getBackedgeValue()->getDefiningRecipe();
1907 }
1908};

2194/// A recipe for vectorizing a phi-node as a sequence of mask-based select
2195/// instructions.
2196class VPBlendRecipe : public VPSingleDefRecipe {
2197public:
2198 /// The blend operation is a User of the incoming values and of their
2199 /// respective masks, ordered [I0, M0, I1, M1, I2, M2, ...]. Note that M0 can
2200 /// be omitted (implied by passing an odd number of operands) in which case
2201 /// all other incoming values are merged into it.
2202 VPBlendRecipe(PHINode *Phi, ArrayRef<VPValue *> Operands)
2203 : VPSingleDefRecipe(VPDef::VPBlendSC, Operands, Phi, Phi->getDebugLoc()) {
2204 assert(Operands.size() > 0 && "Expected at least one operand!");
2205 }
2206
2207 VPBlendRecipe *clone() override {
2208 SmallVector<VPValue *> Ops(operands());
2209 return new VPBlendRecipe(cast<PHINode>(getUnderlyingValue()), Ops);
2210 }
2211
2212 VP_CLASSOF_IMPL(VPDef::VPBlendSC)
2213
2214 /// A normalized blend is one that has an odd number of operands, whereby the
2215 /// first operand does not have an associated mask.
2216 bool isNormalized() const { return getNumOperands() % 2; }
2217
2218 /// Return the number of incoming values, taking into account when normalized
2219 /// the first incoming value will have no mask.
2220 unsigned getNumIncomingValues() const {
2221 return (getNumOperands() + isNormalized()) / 2;
2222 }
2223
2224 /// Return incoming value number \p Idx.
2225 VPValue *getIncomingValue(unsigned Idx) const {
2226 return Idx == 0 ? getOperand(0) : getOperand(Idx * 2 - isNormalized());
2227 }
2228
2229 /// Return mask number \p Idx.
2230 VPValue *getMask(unsigned Idx) const {
2231 assert((Idx > 0 || !isNormalized()) && "First index has no mask!");
2232 return Idx == 0 ? getOperand(1) : getOperand(Idx * 2 + !isNormalized());
2233 }
2234
2235 /// Generate the phi/select nodes.
2236 void execute(VPTransformState &State) override;
2237
2238#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
2239 /// Print the recipe.
2240 void print(raw_ostream &O, const Twine &Indent,
2241 VPSlotTracker &SlotTracker) const override;
2242#endif
2243
2244 /// Returns true if the recipe only uses the first lane of operand \p Op.
2245 bool onlyFirstLaneUsed(const VPValue *Op) const override {
2246 assert(is_contained(operands(), Op) &&
2247 "Op must be an operand of the recipe");
2248 // Recursing through Blend recipes only, must terminate at header phi's the
2249 // latest.
2250 return all_of(users(),
2251 [this](VPUser *U) { return U->onlyFirstLaneUsed(this); });
2252 }
2253};

2255/// VPInterleaveRecipe is a recipe for transforming an interleave group of load
2256/// or stores into one wide load/store and shuffles. The first operand of a
2257/// VPInterleave recipe is the address, followed by the stored values, followed
2258/// by an optional mask.
2259class VPInterleaveRecipe : public VPRecipeBase {
2260 const InterleaveGroup<Instruction> *IG;
2261
2262 /// Indicates if the interleave group is in a conditional block and requires a
2263 /// mask.
2264 bool HasMask = false;
2265
2266 /// Indicates if gaps between members of the group need to be masked out or if
2267 /// unusued gaps can be loaded speculatively.
2268 bool NeedsMaskForGaps = false;
2269
2270public:
2271 VPInterleaveRecipe(const InterleaveGroup<Instruction> *IG, VPValue *Addr,
2272 ArrayRef<VPValue *> StoredValues, VPValue *Mask,
2273 bool NeedsMaskForGaps)
2274 : VPRecipeBase(VPDef::VPInterleaveSC, {Addr}), IG(IG),
2275 NeedsMaskForGaps(NeedsMaskForGaps) {
2276 for (unsigned i = 0; i < IG->getFactor(); ++i)
2277 if (Instruction *I = IG->getMember(i)) {
2278 if (I->getType()->isVoidTy())
2279 continue;
2280 new VPValue(I, this);
2281 }
2282
2283 for (auto *SV : StoredValues)
2284 addOperand(SV);
2285 if (Mask) {
2286 HasMask = true;
2287 addOperand(Mask);
2288 }
2289 }
2290 ~VPInterleaveRecipe() override = default;
2291
2292 VPInterleaveRecipe *clone() override {
2293 return new VPInterleaveRecipe(IG, getAddr(), getStoredValues(), getMask(),
2294 NeedsMaskForGaps);
2295 }
2296
2297 VP_CLASSOF_IMPL(VPDef::VPInterleaveSC)
2298
2299 /// Return the address accessed by this recipe.
2300 VPValue *getAddr() const {
2301 return getOperand(0); // Address is the 1st, mandatory operand.
2302 }
2303
2304 /// Return the mask used by this recipe. Note that a full mask is represented
2305 /// by a nullptr.
2306 VPValue *getMask() const {
2307 // Mask is optional and therefore the last, currently 2nd operand.
2308 return HasMask ? getOperand(getNumOperands() - 1) : nullptr;
2309 }
2310
2311 /// Return the VPValues stored by this interleave group. If it is a load
2312 /// interleave group, return an empty ArrayRef.
2313 ArrayRef<VPValue *> getStoredValues() const {
2314 // The first operand is the address, followed by the stored values, followed
2315 // by an optional mask.
2316 return ArrayRef<VPValue *>(op_begin(), getNumOperands())
2317 .slice(1, getNumStoreOperands());
2318 }
2319
2320 /// Generate the wide load or store, and shuffles.
2321 void execute(VPTransformState &State) override;
2322
2323#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
2324 /// Print the recipe.
2325 void print(raw_ostream &O, const Twine &Indent,
2326 VPSlotTracker &SlotTracker) const override;
2327#endif
2328
2329 const InterleaveGroup<Instruction> *getInterleaveGroup() { return IG; }
2330
2331 /// Returns the number of stored operands of this interleave group. Returns 0
2332 /// for load interleave groups.
2333 unsigned getNumStoreOperands() const {
2334 return getNumOperands() - (HasMask ? 2 : 1);
2335 }
2336
2337 /// The recipe only uses the first lane of the address.
2338 bool onlyFirstLaneUsed(const VPValue *Op) const override {
2339 assert(is_contained(operands(), Op) &&
2340 "Op must be an operand of the recipe");
2341 return Op == getAddr() && !llvm::is_contained(getStoredValues(), Op);
2342 }
2343
2344 Instruction *getInsertPos() const { return IG->getInsertPos(); }
2345};

2620/// A common base class for widening memory operations. An optional mask can be
2621/// provided as the last operand.
2622class VPWidenMemoryRecipe : public VPRecipeBase {
2623protected:
2624 Instruction &Ingredient;
2625
2626 /// Whether the accessed addresses are consecutive.
2627 bool Consecutive;
2628
2629 /// Whether the consecutive accessed addresses are in reverse order.
2630 bool Reverse;
2631
2632 /// Whether the memory access is masked.
2633 bool IsMasked = false;
2634
2635 void setMask(VPValue *Mask) {
2636 assert(!IsMasked && "cannot re-set mask");
2637 if (!Mask)
2638 return;
2639 addOperand(Mask);
2640 IsMasked = true;
2641 }
2642
2643 VPWidenMemoryRecipe(const char unsigned SC, Instruction &I,
2644 std::initializer_list<VPValue *> Operands,
2645 bool Consecutive, bool Reverse, DebugLoc DL)
2646 : VPRecipeBase(SC, Operands, DL), Ingredient(I), Consecutive(Consecutive),
2647 Reverse(Reverse) {
2648 assert((Consecutive || !Reverse) && "Reverse implies consecutive");
2649 }
2650
2651public:
2652 VPWidenMemoryRecipe *clone() override {
2653 llvm_unreachable("cloning not supported");
2654 }
2655
2656 static inline bool classof(const VPRecipeBase *R) {
2657 return R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenLoadSC ||
2658 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenStoreSC ||
2659 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenLoadEVLSC ||
2660 R->getVPDefID() == VPRecipeBase::VPWidenStoreEVLSC;
2661 }
2662
2663 static inline bool classof(const VPUser *U) {
2664 auto *R = dyn_cast<VPRecipeBase>(U);
2665 return R && classof(R);
2666 }
2667
2668 /// Return whether the loaded-from / stored-to addresses are consecutive.
2669 bool isConsecutive() const { return Consecutive; }
2670
2671 /// Return whether the consecutive loaded/stored addresses are in reverse
2672 /// order.
2673 bool isReverse() const { return Reverse; }
2674
2675 /// Return the address accessed by this recipe.
2676 VPValue *getAddr() const { return getOperand(0); }
2677
2678 /// Returns true if the recipe is masked.
2679 bool isMasked() const { return IsMasked; }
2680
2681 /// Return the mask used by this recipe. Note that a full mask is represented
2682 /// by a nullptr.
2683 VPValue *getMask() const {
2684 // Mask is optional and therefore the last operand.
2685 return isMasked() ? getOperand(getNumOperands() - 1) : nullptr;
2686 }
2687
2688 /// Generate the wide load/store.
2689 void execute(VPTransformState &State) override {
2690 llvm_unreachable("VPWidenMemoryRecipe should not be instantiated.");
2691 }
2692
2693 /// Return the cost of this VPWidenMemoryRecipe.
2694 InstructionCost computeCost(ElementCount VF,
2695 VPCostContext &Ctx) const override;
2696
2697 Instruction &getIngredient() const { return Ingredient; }
2698};

3339/// VPRegionBlock represents a collection of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks
3340/// which form a Single-Entry-Single-Exiting subgraph of the output IR CFG.

3343/// scalar if-then code structure needs to be generated VF * UF times. Having

3446/// VPlan models a candidate for vectorization, encoding various decisions take
3447/// to produce efficient output IR, including which branches, basic-blocks and
3448/// output IR instructions to generate, and their cost. VPlan holds a
3449/// Hierarchical-CFG of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks rooted at an Entry

3468 /// any UF.

3472 std::string Name;
3473
3474 /// Represents the trip count of the original loop, for folding
3475 /// the tail.
3476 VPValue *TripCount = nullptr;
3477

3479 /// the tail. It equals TripCount - 1.

3780/// Class that provides utilities for VPBlockBases in VPlan.
3781class VPBlockUtils {
3782public:
3783 VPBlockUtils() = delete;
3784
3785 /// Insert disconnected VPBlockBase \p NewBlock after \p BlockPtr. Add \p
3786 /// NewBlock as successor of \p BlockPtr and \p BlockPtr as predecessor of \p
3787 /// NewBlock, and propagate \p BlockPtr parent to \p NewBlock. \p BlockPtr's
3788 /// successors are moved from \p BlockPtr to \p NewBlock. \p NewBlock must
3789 /// have neither successors nor predecessors.
3790 static void insertBlockAfter(VPBlockBase *NewBlock, VPBlockBase *BlockPtr) {
3791 assert(NewBlock->getSuccessors().empty() &&
3792 NewBlock->getPredecessors().empty() &&
3793 "Can't insert new block with predecessors or successors.");
3794 NewBlock->setParent(BlockPtr->getParent());
3795 SmallVector<VPBlockBase *> Succs(BlockPtr->successors());
3796 for (VPBlockBase *Succ : Succs) {
3797 disconnectBlocks(BlockPtr, Succ);
3798 connectBlocks(NewBlock, Succ);
3799 }
3800 connectBlocks(BlockPtr, NewBlock);
3801 }
3802
3803 /// Insert disconnected block \p NewBlock before \p Blockptr. First
3804 /// disconnects all predecessors of \p BlockPtr and connects them to \p
3805 /// NewBlock. Add \p NewBlock as predecessor of \p BlockPtr and \p BlockPtr as
3806 /// successor of \p NewBlock.
3807 static void insertBlockBefore(VPBlockBase *NewBlock, VPBlockBase *BlockPtr) {
3808 assert(NewBlock->getSuccessors().empty() &&
3809 NewBlock->getPredecessors().empty() &&
3810 "Can't insert new block with predecessors or successors.");
3811 NewBlock->setParent(BlockPtr->getParent());
3812 for (VPBlockBase *Pred : to_vector(BlockPtr->predecessors())) {
3813 disconnectBlocks(Pred, BlockPtr);
3814 connectBlocks(Pred, NewBlock);
3815 }
3816 connectBlocks(NewBlock, BlockPtr);
3817 }
3818
3819 /// Insert disconnected VPBlockBases \p IfTrue and \p IfFalse after \p
3820 /// BlockPtr. Add \p IfTrue and \p IfFalse as succesors of \p BlockPtr and \p
3821 /// BlockPtr as predecessor of \p IfTrue and \p IfFalse. Propagate \p BlockPtr
3822 /// parent to \p IfTrue and \p IfFalse. \p BlockPtr must have no successors
3823 /// and \p IfTrue and \p IfFalse must have neither successors nor
3824 /// predecessors.
3825 static void insertTwoBlocksAfter(VPBlockBase *IfTrue, VPBlockBase *IfFalse,
3826 VPBlockBase *BlockPtr) {
3827 assert(IfTrue->getSuccessors().empty() &&
3828 "Can't insert IfTrue with successors.");
3829 assert(IfFalse->getSuccessors().empty() &&
3830 "Can't insert IfFalse with successors.");
3831 BlockPtr->setTwoSuccessors(IfTrue, IfFalse);
3832 IfTrue->setPredecessors({BlockPtr});
3833 IfFalse->setPredecessors({BlockPtr});
3834 IfTrue->setParent(BlockPtr->getParent());
3835 IfFalse->setParent(BlockPtr->getParent());
3836 }
3837
3838 /// Connect VPBlockBases \p From and \p To bi-directionally. Append \p To to
3839 /// the successors of \p From and \p From to the predecessors of \p To. Both
3840 /// VPBlockBases must have the same parent, which can be null. Both
3841 /// VPBlockBases can be already connected to other VPBlockBases.
3842 static void connectBlocks(VPBlockBase *From, VPBlockBase *To) {
3843 assert((From->getParent() == To->getParent()) &&
3844 "Can't connect two block with different parents");
3845 assert(From->getNumSuccessors() < 2 &&
3846 "Blocks can't have more than two successors.");
3847 From->appendSuccessor(To);
3848 To->appendPredecessor(From);
3849 }
3850
3851 /// Disconnect VPBlockBases \p From and \p To bi-directionally. Remove \p To
3852 /// from the successors of \p From and \p From from the predecessors of \p To.
3853 static void disconnectBlocks(VPBlockBase *From, VPBlockBase *To) {
3854 assert(To && "Successor to disconnect is null.");
3855 From->removeSuccessor(To);
3856 To->removePredecessor(From);
3857 }
3858
3859 /// Return an iterator range over \p Range which only includes \p BlockTy
3860 /// blocks. The accesses are casted to \p BlockTy.
3861 template <typename BlockTy, typename T>
3862 static auto blocksOnly(const T &Range) {
3863 // Create BaseTy with correct const-ness based on BlockTy.
3864 using BaseTy = std::conditional_t<std::is_const<BlockTy>::value,
3865 const VPBlockBase, VPBlockBase>;
3866
3867 // We need to first create an iterator range over (const) BlocktTy & instead
3868 // of (const) BlockTy * for filter_range to work properly.
3869 auto Mapped =
3870 map_range(Range, [](BaseTy *Block) -> BaseTy & { return *Block; });
3871 auto Filter = make_filter_range(
3872 Mapped, [](BaseTy &Block) { return isa<BlockTy>(&Block); });
3873 return map_range(Filter, [](BaseTy &Block) -> BlockTy * {
3874 return cast<BlockTy>(&Block);
3875 });
3876 }
3877};
